      "body":"# Discussion:\r\n\r\n1. Where to parse? My current idea (implemented in this PR) based on performance concerns is: treat everything into one big string as long as they are inside the {{component}} double brackets. Then, we use Regexes to go through every component (stock or custom) and determine if there is a match.\r\n    * If there are complex syntaxes still (e.g. {{query}}, we should build a seperate parser in the component file to ensure maximum compatibility (custom components can have complex syntaxes too!) and performance (if there aren't any block with this complex syntax, it won't be processed at all)\r\n    * Cons: maybe this would bring code fragmentation? Also might be harder to maintain.\r\n\r\n2. File structure\r\n    * where to put: custom components, `components_util.cljc`\r\n\r\n3. Unified class name for better theming support?\r\n\r\nDemo: <https://haojixu.github.io/athens>",
